		<!-- message -->
		<div>I don&#8217;t think Chiteng ever claimed a link between Ewle and himself, he just used her as a martyr for his ongoing crusade against me.<br />
<br />
Ewle was a person that, from day one, didn&#8217;t play by the rules. She trained people without mercy in just about every zone in the game, sometimes while xping and sometimes just for the purpose of removing them from a camp she wanted&#8230; so she didn&#8217;t have to kill steal. All in the name of role playing evil, what a crock of horse shit.<br />
<br />
Anyway, she happened across the wrong guy on her final day &#8211; me.<br />
<br />
I was with a group doing the Sage/Executioner for a few hours, we were setup in the Sage room waiting for the next spawn when Ewle came in, cast a pet, equipped it with two daggers and just sat there. Any idiot knew she was in kill-steal mode. I attempted to open the channels of communication first. I warned her that attempting to kill steal my group was &#8220;a very bad idea.&#8221; I think she may have even laughed, bad move.<br />
<br />
I informed my group that it was about to get ugly. I disbanded so they had zero accountability for any of my actions in the next half-hour. Then it was on&#8230;<br />
<br />
Train 1 &#8211; Three pissed off frogs from the Cavalier room descended upon Ewle with blinding speed, but she managed to get off an FD. Lucky for me Ewle was used to being the trainer and not the trainee, she had no idea how long to sit there until she lost agro (nor did she have a clue about how to use the 3rd person camera). Within about 30 seconds she stood back up and did her best Rodney King impersonation as the 3 frogs, which were right around the corner, pummeled the shit out of her.<br />
<br />
Train 2 &#8211; After she got back to Guk (amidst my /tell taunting she conceded that she was bound at the Freeport dock) it was CR time for her&#8230; in a hostile zone. She brought an Ebonlore Cleric with her to res so I warned him via /tell to leave the zone, immediately. He didn&#8217;t so he became a casualty of war. He cast res on the corpse, she hit &#8216;accept&#8217; then about 4 angry frogs hit her&#8230; and the Cleric. I sent him a /tell, got consent and put him at the zone in with my apologies. He didn&#8217;t come back down.<br />
<br />
Train 3 &#8211; After her run from Freeport, again, she was still too stupid to drag herself to the zone. A simple /who would have revealed that I was still somewhere in the zone&#8230; watching&#8230; waiting. She dragged her corpse down the hall behind some pillars, out of the normal mob pathing and tried to loot again &#8211; BAM!<br />
<br />
This is about the time she petitioned me for training, which I found infinitely amusing&#8230; kind of like Manson calling the cops on someone.<br />
<br />
Train 4 &#8211; By far the most brilliant of them all, but I had help. If you don&#8217;t know who it was, tough, he doesn&#8217;t need the publicity. She managed to loot her corpse, somehow, but opted to run out for whatever reason. We met her on the bridge near the gargoyles, all of us were Inviso to Undead. She stopped to taunt us and her inviso dropped, mobs started to cast on her immediately but she managed an FD between casts&#8230; damn. She knew we would stand there and wait for her to get up, so she LD.<br />
<br />
Being gambling men we were willing to bet she would be back within 5 minutes. So we grabbed the nearest casting frog and maneuvered him into position right where she would come back, then we Screaming Terror&#8217;d it in place for the next five or so minutes. Finally we see her pop back into the game, but everyone knows that your avatar loads before you have any control. We FD&#8217;d and the mob got medieval on her ass, she tried to FD again but the frogs casting still got her. Dead, again.<br />
<br />
Soon after I got a /tell from the GM of the server letting me know that she was now watching, she was trying to catch Ewle doing anything illegal so she could ban. I offered to be bait for a Ewletrain&#8482; but in the end Ewle cut her own throat, she mentioned in guild chat that Uini was in the zone and X number of hit points&#8230; clearly she was using ShowEQ, a banable offense.<br />
<br />
I win.</div>
